Two suspected gangsters who were shot dead on Wednesday night when gunmen stormed a house in William Slabbert Drive, Booysen Park, have been identified. Wandile Ngwenzi, 20, and Enrico Stuurman, 25, were killed in the shooting while two other people, aged 38 and 27, were wounded. Ngwenzi died on the scene and Stuurman later in Livingstone Hospital. Police said three gunmen stormed the house shortly before 7pm, shooting randomly. Police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu said one of the wounded men was still critical. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share